      .col-md-4
        h2 What is a challenge?
        p.
          A data-driven challenge is a problem with well-defined inputs and
          outputs to which competitors can submit results that are then
          scored against a known ground-truth and ranked. Kitware's
          challenge platform allows outputs or code that produces outputs to
          be submitted, and will automatically score the result submissions.

      .col-md-4
        h2 Why challenges?
        p.
          As the age of Big Data&trade; leads to a proliferation of
          statistical and machine-learning methods for solving complex
          problems, it becomes ever more important to run the latest and
          greatest algorithms on <i>real-world data</i>. When designed
          properly, challenges can show you how state-of-the-art methods
          work on data that is much more representational of the problem
          domain at large, rather than with toy, synthetic, or sample data.

      .col-md-4
        h2 How does this work?
        p.
          Kitware and our academic and industry partners have combined
          decades of High-Performance Computing and medical imaging
          experience with our modern data and analytics framework,
          TangeloHub, to produce a platform for hosting data-driven
          challenges.

