          h2#what What is a challenge?
          p.
            A data-driven challenge (often called a grand challenge) is a
            structured "contest" that allows contestants to submit results or
            even executables, scripts, and/or code to be scored against the
            results or methods of other contestants. When challenge
            organizers chose representative datasets and define the problem
            well, data-driven challenges have the potential to bring the best
            method available to solve real-world problems.
          p.
            The result of good challenges is a win for both parties.
            Algorithm developers discover how methods work on real data, and
            challenge organizers find out what the field has to offer.
            Challenges provide an excellent start to many productive working
            relationships.

