          h2#why Why challenges?
          p.
            Modern scientific research software is often published with
            detailed analyses over the datasets to which the investigators
            had access. This often makes it difficult assess the utility of a
            given method on your data. Businesses spend millions in research
            and development in attempts to rework published methods on their
            specific data. We think there's a better way.
          p.
            Data-driven challenges connect stakeholders who have immediate
            real problems with communities of algorithm developers eager to
            prove their methods' generality and applicability to new domains.
            Bringing these two complimentary groups together with an
            automated web-based system enhances reproducibility and will save
            time and money.  Stakeholders can see how the methods compare to
            each other for datasets of interest, and algorithm developers
            have a platform that empowers improvements in their methods.

